dered (presumably by his girlfriend, who was a material suspect in Torres's previous undercover assignment years earlier). A strand of blonde hair is found at the crime scene; the girlfriend is blonde, leading the team to suspect her, though McGee is uneasy that Bishop may have followed through with her intention to kill Zolotov. However, after she confirms she did not do so at the end of the episode, McGee begins to suspect that Gibbs may have killed Zolotov to protect her.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 393\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n |Title           = Lonely Hearts\n |DirectedBy      = Michael Zinberg\n |WrittenBy       = Marco Schnabel\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|11}}\n |Viewers         = 11.75<ref name=\"17.15\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-11-2020.html|title=UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.11.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=February 12, 2020|accessdate=February 12, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200212211933/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-11-2020.html|archive-date=February 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The lead suspect for the murders of two Marines is a woman that Gibbs' friend, Phillip Brooks ([[Don Lake]]), met on a dating website. Also, Sloane has a secret admirer on Valentine's Day, and Torres is out of the hospital from the hit-and-run incident.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 394\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 16\n |Title           = Ephemera\n |DirectedBy      = Diana Valentine\n |WrittenBy       = Christopher J. Waild\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|18}}\n |Viewers         = 11.91<ref name=\"17.16\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-18-2020.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.18.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=February 20, 2020|accessdate=February 20, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = While investigating the suicide of a retired Navy officer who left a rare, valuable - and possibly stolen - coin to the National Museum of the Navy, the team imagines themselves in his life story in order to piece together how the coin ended up in his possession.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 395\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 17\n |Title           = In a Nutshell\n |DirectedBy      = Michael Zinberg\n |WrittenBy       = Katie White\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|10}}\n |Viewers         = 10.75<ref name=\"17.17\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-10-2020.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.10.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=March 11, 2020|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = NCIS investigates the murder of a petty officer who was killed in the exact same manner as his parents were 10 years prior. The victim's sister, Claire, has recreated \"nutshells\" depicting her parents' deaths, which assists the team in the investigation. Meanwhile, the team agrees to clean out some of their personal belongings to donate to a charity, but some have a harder time letting go than others. The episode ends with Bishop receiving a text from Odette.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 396\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 18\n |Title           = Schooled\n |DirectedBy      = [[Alrick Riley]]\n |WrittenBy       = Kate Torgovnick May & Steven D. Binder\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|24}}\n |Viewers         = 13.22<ref name=\"17.18\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-24-2020.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.24.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=March 24, 2020|accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = When a seemingly well-regarded Marine is found dead in a lake near where a popular community event is being held, the team comes to realize he is a wanted hacker. Meanwhile, Sloane\u2019s biological daughter Faith, requests her father\u2019s medical history, unintentionally forcing Sloane to confront that man: he had raped her after a college party. Sloane makes sure he\u2019ll give Faith what she asks for, lie about the circumstances of her birth, and to never contact her again, but Faith puts two and two together and thanks Sloane for giving her up for adoption in order to protect her from her biological father.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 397\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 19\n |Title           = Blarney\n |DirectedBy      = Rocky Carroll\n |WrittenBy       = Scott Williams\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|31}}\n |Viewers         = 13.65<ref name=\"17.19\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-31-2020.html|title=ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.31.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Jimmy and Kasie are held hostage in the diner Gibbs frequently visits after three armed burglars mismanage a heist at a nearby jewelry store. The leader kills their driver beforehand due to the latter spilling details to his wife, who later relays it to Vance and Sloane. A cook at the diner shoots one of the burglars in an attempt to free the patrons, later resulting in the crook\u2019s death and his fellow robbers forcing Jimmy to cut out the diamonds he had swallowed. This gives Jimmy and Kasie the idea to convince them they are bleeding internally from broken glass, saving the other patrons and ending the hostage situation.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n{{#invoke:Episode list|sublist|NCIS (season 17)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 398\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 20\n |Title           = The Arizona\n |DirectedBy      = James Whitmore, Jr.\n |WrittenBy       = Gina Lucita Monreal\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|14}}\n |Viewers         = 13.49<ref name=\"17.20\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-14-2020.html|title=ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.14.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = The team tries to verify the identity of Joe Smith, who claims to have served on the U.S.S. Arizona during the Pearl Harbor attacks and wants his ashes interred there when he dies. Meanwhile, McGee unwittingly gets roped into a family reunion of people he doesn\u2019t know.\n\nNote: This episode was dedicated to the Pearl Harbor victims as well as the first responders and those on the frontlines battling the Coronavirus pandemic.\n |LineColor       = 36454F\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Production==\n''NCIS'' was renewed for a seventeenth season on April 11, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/ncis-renewed-season-17-cbs-mark-harmon-new-deal-cbs-tv-studios-1202593874/|title=''NCIS'' Renewed For Season 17 By CBS As Star & EP Mark Harmon Inks New Deal|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 11, 2019|accessdate=April 11, 2019|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411193012/https://deadline.com/2019/04/ncis-renewed-season-17-cbs-mark-harmon-new-deal-cbs-tv-studios-1202593874/|archi